<p>I restored our new SQL Server 2012 database from the old SQL Server 2008 version.</p>  <p>I have a FTS on one of the tables and the search on the SQL Server 2012 database shows the same results as the 2008 data but when I insert a new row into the SQL Server 2012 version with matching text, I only see the pre-existing rows and not the new ones.</p>  <p>Examples from the SQL Server 2012 database (note:rows 1 and 2 are from the restore):</p>  <pre><code>select *  from tablename  where contains(field1, 'abc'); </code></pre>  <p>results</p>  <pre><code>pk     field1      datestamp   1       'abc'       9/26 2       'abc'       9/27    select *  from tablename  where field1 like '%abc%';  </code></pre>  <p>results</p>  <pre><code>pk     field1      datestamp  1       'abc'       9/26  2       'abc'       9/27  3       'abc'       9/28  </code></pre>  <p>Clues?</p>